Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, has said that the federal government lacked the resources to deliver on   developmental and infrastructural projects it had committed to owing  to the economic downturn. Gbajabiamila, who stated this yesterday at the opening of aninvestigative hearing seeking to identify and plug revenue leakages  that cost the federal government in excess of $30 billion annually,  lamented that the country is facing significant revenue challenges due to global collapse in the price of crude oil, brought about by a  severe and ongoing contraction in the global economy and the consequent reduction in demand for fossil fuels. 